269
00:11:23,061 --> 00:11:25,062
then plutonium is produced.

270
00:11:25,062 --> 00:11:27,588
Later it was found that plutonium

271
00:11:27,588 --> 00:11:30,494
is more radioactive and more fissionable

272
00:11:30,494 --> 00:11:32,640
as compared to Uranium 235.

273
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,302
Apart from these two locations,

274
00:11:34,302 --> 00:11:36,541
they were looking for a third location.

275
00:11:36,541 --> 00:11:38,517
For Project Y.

276
00:11:38,517 --> 00:11:41,376
A location where the actual work of

277
00:11:41,376 --> 00:11:44,152
designing and making these bombs would take place.

278
00:11:44,152 --> 00:11:47,548
General Groves wanted a remote location for this.

279
00:11:47,548 --> 00:11:49,937
So that the project could remain a secret.

280
00:11:49,937 --> 00:11:53,575
Oppenheimer knew exactly such a location.

281
00:11:53,575 --> 00:11:57,670
It is a place where Oppenheimer spent his summers happily.

282
00:11:57,670 --> 00:11:59,989
Surrounded by mountains and beautiful landscapes,

283
00:11:59,989 --> 00:12:02,933
the Pecos Valley in New Mexico.

284
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:04,802
After setting up all these locations,

285
00:12:04,802 --> 00:12:06,820
there was only one obvious thing left to do.

286
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:10,258
To practically test out a chain reaction.

287
00:12:10,258 --> 00:12:12,614
Everything was theoretical till now.

288
00:12:12,614 --> 00:12:14,634
So they needed proof on whether

289
00:12:14,634 --> 00:12:16,541
the whole concept of the atomic bomb

290
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,755
was feasible or not.

291
00:12:18,755 --> 00:12:20,813
2nd December 1942.

292
00:12:20,813 --> 00:12:25,480
Scientist Enrico Fermi conducted the first successful practical experiment.

293
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:28,413
In a squash court of the University of Chicago,

294
00:12:28,413 --> 00:12:30,253
he ran a chain reaction,

295
00:12:30,253 --> 00:12:33,216
which helps light up a bulb.

296
00:12:33,216 --> 00:12:35,207
"The clickety-clack of their instruments,

297
00:12:35,207 --> 00:12:36,968
proved they had achieved 

298
00:12:36,968 --> 00:12:40,485
the first human-made nuclear chain reaction."

299
00:12:40,872 --> 00:12:43,317
By this point, General Groves

300
00:12:43,317 --> 00:12:46,177
was impressed with Oppenheimer's ability.

301
00:12:46,177 --> 00:12:49,758
He wanted to appoint him as the director of Project Y.

302
00:12:49,758 --> 00:12:52,245
But some senior members of the military

303
00:12:52,245 --> 00:12:53,549
doubted Oppenheimer.

304
00:12:53,549 --> 00:12:55,908
The same way that they doubted Albert Einstein.

305
00:12:55,908 --> 00:12:57,826
Many friends of Oppenheimer,

306
00:12:57,826 --> 00:13:00,047
his wife, and in fact, his brother,

307
00:13:00,047 --> 00:13:02,168
were all hard-core communists.

308
00:13:02,168 --> 00:13:04,894
He was influenced by the left-wing ideology himself.

309
00:13:04,894 --> 00:13:07,637
America was afraid that this communist ideology

310
00:13:07,637 --> 00:13:09,518
could go against their country.

311
00:13:09,518 --> 00:13:11,305
But despite these concerns,

312
00:13:11,305 --> 00:13:14,718
General Groves personally supported Oppenheimer

313
00:13:14,718 --> 00:13:16,379
and said that

314
00:13:16,379 --> 00:13:18,734
this project could not happen without Oppenheimer.

315
00:13:18,734 --> 00:13:20,551
And that he was essential for this project.

316
00:13:20,551 --> 00:13:23,459
And because of this, on 20th July 1943,

317
00:13:23,459 --> 00:13:26,536
Oppenheimer was made the lead of this project.

318
00:13:26,536 --> 00:13:28,314
To make an atom bomb,

319
00:13:28,314 --> 00:13:30,604
Oppenheimer's expertise was required

320
00:13:30,604 --> 00:13:32,673
in the calculation of critical mass.

321
00:13:32,673 --> 00:13:36,025
Critical mass is basically a minimum amount of mass

322
00:13:36,025 --> 00:13:38,518
of Uranium-235 or Plutonium

323
00:13:38,518 --> 00:13:41,217
which is needed to have a chain reaction,

324
00:13:41,217 --> 00:13:43,157
to sustain a chain reaction.

325
00:13:43,157 --> 00:13:46,836
The minimum amount of radioactive elements that would be needed

326
00:13:46,836 --> 00:13:49,460
to carry out a chain reaction and a bomb blast.

327
00:13:49,460 --> 00:13:51,668
It seems easy today,

328
00:13:51,668 --> 00:13:53,749
but there were many unknown factors at that time.

329
00:13:53,749 --> 00:13:57,157
We hardly knew anything about the properties of Uranium-235.

330
00:13:57,157 --> 00:14:02,015
Plutonium-239 was actually discovered in 1940.

331
00:14:02,015 --> 00:14:03,887
And by the end of 1943,

332
00:14:03,887 --> 00:14:06,913
only 2 milligrams of plutonium could be produced.

333
00:14:06,913 --> 00:14:10,235
That's why America was developing two atom bombs.

334
00:14:10,235 --> 00:14:13,388
The first bomb was based on Uranium-235,

335
00:14:13,388 --> 00:14:15,178
named Little Boy.

336
00:14:16,459 --> 00:14:17,951
The mechanism of this bomb was basically

337
00:14:17,951 --> 00:14:19,332
a gun-type design.

338
00:14:19,332 --> 00:14:22,993
Two masses of Uranium-235 were taken,

339
00:14:22,993 --> 00:14:24,424
which were sub-critical.

340
00:14:24,424 --> 00:14:25,723
Less than the critical value.

341
00:14:25,723 --> 00:14:28,332
And they were combined rapidly with each other.

342
00:14:28,332 --> 00:14:30,994
With this combination, the critical mass was reached

343
00:14:30,994 --> 00:14:33,769
and a fission chain reaction follows

344
00:14:33,769 --> 00:14:35,518
resulting in an explosion.

345
00:14:38,022 --> 00:14:39,740
The second bomb was the plutonium bomb

346
00:14:39,740 --> 00:14:42,482
which was using plutonium-239

347
00:14:42,482 --> 00:14:44,080
and its name was Fat Man.

348
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:46,084
It was more difficult to design.

349
00:14:46,084 --> 00:14:48,263
Here, it could not be designed as a gun

350
00:14:48,263 --> 00:14:52,376
because if the masses of two plutonium were combined,

351
00:14:52,376 --> 00:14:54,476
it would react very quickly

352
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:58,272
and the fission reaction would end before the critical mass could be reached.

353
00:14:58,272 --> 00:15:02,231
"A Plutonium gun-bomb would melt, not explode."

354
00:15:02,639 --> 00:15:06,484
Here, scientists created a different design for the plutonium bomb.

355
00:15:06,484 --> 00:15:10,033
The mass of plutonium was to be placed under high pressure and density

356
00:15:10,033 --> 00:15:11,527
in a spherical structure.

357
00:15:11,527 --> 00:15:15,550
A sub-critical mass of plutonium was placed inside a hollow sphere.

358
00:15:15,550 --> 00:15:17,968
And outside the sphere, explosives were used

359
00:15:17,968 --> 00:15:21,500
to create an implosion in the mass of plutonium.

360
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,670
When the explosives outside exploded,

361
00:15:23,670 --> 00:15:25,597
the plutonium would be under high pressure

362
00:15:25,597 --> 00:15:27,700
and it would reach the critical mass.

363
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:30,299
This concept was called the implosion method.

364
00:15:30,299 --> 00:15:33,578
Scientists already knew about the gun method,

365
00:15:33,578 --> 00:15:37,387
but this was the first time that the implosion method was theoretically mentioned.

366
00:15:37,387 --> 00:15:40,337
Oppenheimer believed that it was necessary to test it out

367
00:15:40,337 --> 00:15:42,926
before actually putting it in the bomb.

368
00:15:42,926 --> 00:15:44,849
General Groves said that

369
00:15:44,849 --> 00:15:46,516
they can't test such things because

370
00:15:46,516 --> 00:15:49,217
they had produced only a small amount of plutonium.

371
00:15:49,217 --> 00:15:50,947
But Oppenheimer was adamant that

372
00:15:50,947 --> 00:15:52,299
the test was necessary.

373
00:15:52,299 --> 00:15:53,913
So General Groves had to finally agree.

374
00:15:53,913 --> 00:15:56,821
And then, friends, the Trinity Test was conducted.

375
00:15:56,821 --> 00:15:59,057
I talked about this at the beginning of the video.

376
00:15:59,057 --> 00:16:01,142
In the desert of New Mexico,

377
00:16:01,142 --> 00:16:03,697
a test nuclear bomb was dropped

378
00:16:03,697 --> 00:16:06,152
This test bomb was called Gadget.

379
00:16:06,152 --> 00:16:08,776
It contained 13 pounds of plutonium.

380
00:16:08,776 --> 00:16:14,278
Scientists hung Gadget 100 ft in the air using a steel tower.

381
00:16:14,278 --> 00:16:16,902
And on 16th July 1945,

382
00:16:16,902 --> 00:16:18,452
at 5.30 am,

383
00:16:18,452 --> 00:16:20,462
this bomb was detonated.

384
00:16:24,858 --> 00:16:26,230
As I told you,

385
00:16:26,230 --> 00:16:30,172
this bomb was much more powerful than Oppenheimer expected.

386
00:16:30,172 --> 00:16:32,664
The steel tower completely evaporated.

387
00:16:32,664 --> 00:16:37,379
After the bomb blast, a mildly radioactive green-coloured glass was formed,

388
00:16:37,379 --> 00:16:39,143
which was named Trinitite.

389
00:16:39,143 --> 00:16:40,808
It was after seeing this blast,

390
00:16:40,808 --> 00:16:44,440
that Oppenheimer uttered some lines of the Bhagavad Gita.

391
00:16:44,818 --> 00:16:46,547
"Now I am become death,

392
00:16:47,129 --> 00:16:48,601
the destroyer of worlds.

393
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,701
I suppose we all thought that,

394
00:16:52,701 --> 00:16:53,799
one way or another."

395
00:16:54,236 --> 00:16:57,142
Actually, Oppenheimer was a Sanskrit scholar

396
00:16:57,142 --> 00:16:59,745
and he had studied the entire Bhagavad Gita

397
00:16:59,745 --> 00:17:00,859
in its original form.

398
00:17:00,859 --> 00:17:05,074
He describes the Bhagavad Gita as one of the most influential books of his life.

399
00:17:05,074 --> 00:17:08,141
Less than a month after the Trinity test,

400
00:17:08,141 --> 00:17:10,961
on 6th August 1945,

401
00:17:10,961 --> 00:17:14,114
the Little Boy bomb was dropped on Hiroshima.

402
00:17:14,114 --> 00:17:15,647
If that wasn't enough,

403
00:17:15,647 --> 00:17:19,605
then three days later, this plutonium Fat Man bomb

404
00:17:19,605 --> 00:17:21,532
was dropped on Nagasaki too.

405
00:17:25,986 --> 00:17:28,786
What was the effect of dropping these atomic bombs?

406
00:17:28,786 --> 00:17:32,665
I have discussed this in detail in the Hiroshima and Nagasaki video.

407
00:17:34,237 --> 00:17:35,978
Albert Einstein's first reaction

408
00:17:35,978 --> 00:17:37,444
upon hearing this news was

409
00:17:37,444 --> 00:17:39,012
"Woe is me."

410
00:17:39,012 --> 00:17:41,036
A melancholy statement.

411
00:17:41,385 --> 00:17:43,640
It is believed that Albert Einstein also said this.

412
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:45,650
"Mankind invented the atomic bomb,

413
00:17:45,650 --> 00:17:48,468
but no mouse would ever construct a mousetrap."

414
00:17:49,108 --> 00:17:52,614
Oppenheimer expressed happiness after the bomb was dropped on Hiroshima.

415
00:17:52,614 --> 00:17:54,644
He wished that this bomb

416
00:17:54,644 --> 00:17:58,224
could be used against Nazi Germany and Hitler.

417
00:17:58,224 --> 00:18:00,546
But when the bomb was dropped on Nagasaki,

418
00:18:00,546 --> 00:18:02,884
Oppenheimer was shocked.

419
00:18:02,884 --> 00:18:05,520
On 17th August, he went to Washington

420
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:07,145
to meet the Secretary of War.

421
00:18:07,145 --> 00:18:10,582
To hand-deliver the letter he wrote.

422
00:18:10,582 --> 00:18:12,152
He directly said that

423
00:18:12,152 --> 00:18:14,111
he wanted to ban nuclear weapons.

424
00:18:14,111 --> 00:18:16,244
He was very regretful 

425
00:18:16,244 --> 00:18:17,558
about his part in it.

426
00:18:17,558 --> 00:18:20,974
The technology he handed over to humas.

427
00:18:20,974 --> 00:18:25,694
Oppenheimer considered the first bomb dropped on Hiroshima as a necessary evil.

428
00:18:25,694 --> 00:18:28,706
But now he was afraid for the future.

429
00:18:28,706 --> 00:18:32,240
What will different countries do with this technology in the future?

430
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:34,413
In the meantime, in April 1945,

431
00:18:34,413 --> 00:18:37,125
American President Roosevelt passed away.

432
00:18:37,125 --> 00:18:39,902
The next American President was Harry Truman.

433
00:18:39,902 --> 00:18:43,012
Two months after the bomb was dropped on Nagasaki,

434
00:18:43,012 --> 00:18:45,440
Oppenheimer got a chance

435
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:47,002
to meet President Truman.

436
00:18:47,002 --> 00:18:49,686
When meeting the President, he said directly,

437
00:18:49,686 --> 00:18:51,480
"I have blood on my hands."

438
00:18:52,091 --> 00:18:55,767
And President Truman was so angry after hearing this that

439
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:57,899
he started shouting at him.

440
00:18:57,899 --> 00:19:01,868
He told his secretary to throw Oppenheimer out of the office

441
00:19:01,868 --> 00:19:03,946
and that he didn't want to see his face ever again.

442
00:19:03,946 --> 00:19:08,124
Oppenheimer later worked with the US Atomic Energy Commission

443
00:19:08,124 --> 00:19:11,102
to stop other such nuclear attacks.

444
00:19:11,102 --> 00:19:14,618
He wanted to establish control over nuclear weapons.

445
00:19:14,618 --> 00:19:19,039
In 1949, when President Truman approached the commission

446
00:19:19,039 --> 00:19:22,653
with the idea of making a hydrogen bomb,

447
00:19:22,653 --> 00:19:26,155
Oppenheimer strongly opposed it.

448
00:19:26,155 --> 00:19:28,726
But this opposition was of no use

449
00:19:28,726 --> 00:19:32,031
because America developed a hydrogen bomb later

450
00:19:32,031 --> 00:19:35,387
and also conducted tests in 1952.

451
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,890
Edward Teller was the scientist

452
00:19:40,890 --> 00:19:43,378
who helped in making this hydrogen bomb.

453
00:19:43,378 --> 00:19:46,839
And he is called the Father of the Hydrogen Bomb today.

454
00:19:46,839 --> 00:19:48,860
Because of Oppenheimer's resistance

455
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:51,133
and his left-wing ideology,

456
00:19:51,133 --> 00:19:53,649
his job was snatched away from him.

457
00:19:53,649 --> 00:19:57,311
He spent the rest of his life in the academic profession

458
00:19:57,311 --> 00:19:59,649
and used to give lectures all over the world.

459
00:19:59,649 --> 00:20:02,814
Even though he was nominated for the Nobel Prize thrice,

460
00:20:02,814 --> 00:20:04,744
he could not win even once.

461
00:20:04,744 --> 00:20:07,330
In 1965, due to throat cancer,

462
00:20:07,330 --> 00:20:10,916
Oppenheimer died at the age of 62.

463
00:20:10,916 --> 00:20:12,567
Which was not surprising

464
00:20:12,567 --> 00:20:15,935
as he was a terrible chain smoker throughout his life.

465
00:20:15,935 --> 00:20:18,491
Today, there are 9 countries

466
00:20:18,491 --> 00:20:20,499
that have nuclear weapons.

467
00:20:20,499 --> 00:20:22,247
India, Pakistan, China,

468
00:20:22,247 --> 00:20:24,305
the USA, France, the UK,

469
00:20:24,305 --> 00:20:27,053
Israel, Russia, and North Korea.

470
00:20:27,053 --> 00:20:29,886
But the positive thing is that in the last 80 years,

471
00:20:29,886 --> 00:20:34,349
no other nuclear weapon has been used.

